By definition,
 `sum_{x* | Tx*=y*} θ_{x*} = φ_{y*}`.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
`P(Y=y,
 Y*=y*) = 
\backslash
left( c(r_{obs}) 
\backslash
prod_k C(y^*_k,
 y_k) 
\backslash
right) φ_{y*}`
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
5.
 **Final Step:** Since `p_φ(y,
 y*) = p_φ(y|y*) φ_{y*}` by definition,
